Citation.sTitle: Density, Ultrasonic Velocity, Electrical Conductivity, Viscosity, and Raman Spectra of Methanolic Mg(ClO4)2, Mg(NO3)2, and Mg(OAc)2 Solutions
Citation.sAbstract: Density, ultrasonic velocity, electrical conductivity, viscosity, and Raman spectra of methanolic Mg(ClO4)2,  Mg(NO3)2, and Mg(OAc)2 solutions were measured as functions of concentration (dilute to saturation) and  temperature (273.15 e T/K e 313.15). The isentropic compressibility, electrical conductivity, and Raman  spectral data reveal the following order of anion-solvent interactions and mobility in methanol: OAc- less than  NO3  - less than ClO4  -. Anionic effect on the isentropic compressibility and conductivity roughly appear to follow  Hofmeister series. Transport properties and Raman spectra also indicate a moderate solvent-shared ion pairing  in concentrated Mg(NO3)2 solutions.
